{
  "text": "Gene expression studies. Reverse transcriptase-PCR (RT-PCR) technique was employed to study the gene expression of known morphogenetic ECM proteins in metanephric tissues treated with glucose. First, a competitive minigene plasmid DNA construct containing sequences of various ECM proteins and their receptors was synthesized using various primers. The nucleotide sequences of 5 \u0408 sense (SE) and 3 \u0408 antisense (AS) primers were derived from data available in Genbank/EMBL/DDBJ. The respective sequences of 5'SE and 3 \u0408 AS primers were as follows: type-IV collagen, 5 \u0408 -GG-GAGCATGAAGGGACAG-3 \u0408 (5'SE) and 5 \u0408 -CAGGGCCTTGCT-GGCTTC-3 \u0408 (3 \u0408 AS); laminin-A chain, 5 \u0408 -CATGGAAATGCAAG-CCAACC-3 \u0408 (5'SE) and 5 \u0408 -GCCATGGTGGAGAAGACGCTC-3 \u0408 (3 \u0408 AS); perlecan (basement membrane HS-PG), 5 \u0408 -GCTGCTA-GCGGTGACGCATG-3 \u0408 (5'SE) and 5 \u0408 -GTTCCGACGCCTGGG-CACAG-3 \u0408 (3 \u0408 AS); and \u2424 -actin, 5 \u0408 -GACGACATGGAGAAGAT-CTGG-3 \u0408 (5'SE) and 5 \u0408 -ATGGCCACTGCCGCATCCTC-3 \u0408 (3 \u0408 AS). Using these primers and murine embryonic renal cDNA, the PCR products of the expected size of 392 bp (type-IV collagen), 747 bp (laminin A chain), 520 bp (perlecan), and 460 bp ( \u2424 -actin) were generated, and their authenticity was confirmed by nucleotide sequence analyses, as previously described [CITATION_1] . After determining the suitablity of these primers for PCR reactions, two sets of long 5 \u0408 and 3 \u0408 polydeoxynucleotide (PDN) single-stranded DNAs in SE and AS orientations with overlapping extensions were synthesized in Northwestern University's biotechnology facility. The 5 \u0408 SE-PDN (110 mer) included, in seriatum, the nucleotide sequences of type-IV collagen, laminin A chain, perlecan, integrin-\u2423 3 , -\u2423 5 , and -\u2423 6 ; while the 5 \u0408 AS-PDN (105 mer) had sequences of \u2424 -actin, fibronectin, basic fibroblast growth factor-receptor (bFGF-R), integrin-\u2423 6 , -\u2423 5 , and \u2423 3 . The 3 \u0408 SE-PDN (112 mer) included the sequences of type-IV collagen, laminin A chain, perlecan, integrin-\u2423 3 , -\u2423 5 , and -\u2423 6 ; while the 3 \u0408 AS-PDN (109 mer) had sequences of \u2424 -actin, fibronectin, bFGF-R, integrin-\u2423 6 , -\u2423 5 , and -\u2423 3 . The 5 \u0408 SE-and 5 \u0408 AS-PDNs were annealed and amplified by PCR to generate a double-stranded DNA with 183-bp product. Similarly, 3 \u0408 SE-and 3 \u0408 AS-PDNs were annealed and amplified by PCR to generate a double-stranded DNA with 183-bp product. The 5 \u0408 and 3 \u0408 generated products were subjected to blunt end ligation, followed by amplification with PCR, using type-IV collagen 5 \u0408 sense primer and \u2424 -actin 3 \u0408 antisense primer, to generate a final template DNA with 386 bp; the latter was ligated into pCR TM II cloning vector (Invitrogen Corp., San Diego, CA), and its nucleotide sequence was confirmed by dideoxy chain termination method [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . This template DNA was designated as competitive plasmid DNA to be used in gene expression studies of various ECM proteins. Using the competitive plasmid DNA as a template for primers of various ECM proteins, the expected size of their products is relatively small (221-224 bp), and thus can be easily distinguished from the PCR products generated from murine renal embryonic cDNA.",
  "correct_citation": {
